@@TJvColorComboBox
##JVCL:Component
<TITLEIMG TJvColorComboBox>
<GROUP JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Combos, JVCL.SelectAndChoose>
Summary
  Combo box that enables the user to select a color from a drop-down list.
Description
  TJvColorComboBox is a TJvCustomComboBox descendant which enables the user to select a
  color from a drop-down list.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.AddColor
Summary
  Adds a color to the combo box's color list.
Description
  Call AddColor at runtime to add a color to the combo box.
Parameters
  AColor      - Specifies the color to add.
  DisplayName - The display text for the new color. 
See Also
  InsertColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorDialogText
Summary
  Specifies the display text for the special combo box item, used to select a color from a dialog.
Description
  Use ColorDialogText to specify a new \string for the combo box item, used to select a color from
  a dialog. Thus, if the user selects this item, the component displays a dialog for selecting colors.
  
  If the user selects a color from the dialog, a new item is added to the combo box, with text specified
  by NewColorText, and color as selected in the dialog.
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't display this special
  item.
See Also
  CustomColorCount, NewColorText, OnBeforeCustom, OnNewColor, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorNameMap
Summary
  Determines display names for colors.
Description
  Use ColorNameMap to specify display names for colors. Each line must be in the form
  <CODE>
  Color=DisplayName
  </CODE>
  where Color is the symbolic constant defined for the color (such as clBlack or 
  clWindow) or if there is no such symbolic constant defined, the hex value of the color, formatted 
  as a \string such as '$02FF8800'. DisplayName specifies the display name for that color.
  
  For example, the following strings set the display names of clBlack and $00020202 to "Black" and
  "Almost Black", respectively:
  <CODE>
  clBlack=Black
  $00020202=Almost Black
  </CODE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorValue
Summary
  Specifies the color value that is displayed in the edit box.
Description
  Use the ColorValue property to read the color value of the current selected color or specify a new
  color for the ColorValue value, to change the current selected color.
  
  If ColorValue is set to a color that doesn't exists in the combo box's list, then the color is 
  added to the list.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width, in pixels, of the color boxes.
Description
  Use ColorWidth to specify the width of the color boxes.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.CustomColorCount
Summary
  Indicates the number of custom colors in the combo box's color list
Description
  \Read CustomColorCount to determine the number of custom colors in the combo box's color list.
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't allow colors to be added
  by the user.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, NewColorText, OnBeforeCustom, OnNewColor, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.DroppedDownWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width, in pixels, of the drop-down list. 
Description
  Use DropDownWidth to customize the width of the drop-down list.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.GetColors
Summary
  Clears the combo box's list and refills it with colors.
Description
  Use GetColors to reset the combo box's list to it's initial state. It fills the combo box's list
  with the colors as definied in the Graphics unit, such as clBlack and clMaroon. If coSysColors is
  included in Options it also adds colors defined in the Windows Control panel, such as clMenu and
  clWindow. If coCustomColors is included in Options it also adds the special combo box items which
  allows the user to add custom colors to the combo box.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.HiliteColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteColor to read or change the background color of the text that is focused. The focused line
  is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
See Also
  HiliteText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.HiliteText
Summary
  Specifies the color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteText to specify the color of the text characters (as opposed to the background color) of
  the focused line. The focused text is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
  
  If Color is set to a dithered color, the text appears in the closest non-dithered value.
See Also
  HiliteColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.InsertColor
Summary
  Inserts a color at a specified position in the combo box's color list.
Description
  Use the InsertColor method to insert a color into the combo box color list.
Parameters
  AIndex      - Specifies a zero-based position in the combo box's list where to insert the color.
  AColor      - Specifies the color to insert.
  DisplayName - The display text for the new color. 
See Also
  AddColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.NewColorText
Summary
  Specifies the prefix for the display text of new colors added by the user.
Description
  Use NewColorText to specify a prefix for the text of colors added by the user. The user can add
  colors to the combo box by selecting the special combo box item - with text ColorDialogText. 
  
  If the user selects a color from the dialog, a new item is added to the combobox. The display text
  of this item consist of the NewColorText and a number indicating the number of custom colors added
  by the user, so far. 
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't allow colors to be added
  by the user.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, CustomColorCount, OnBeforeCustom, OnNewColor, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.OnBeforeCustom
Summary
  Occurs before the special combo box item, used to select a color from a dialog, is added to the 
  combo box's list.
Description
  Use OnBeforeCustom to respond when the special combo box item, with text as specified by ColorDialogText,
  is added to the combo box's list.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, CustomColorCount, NewColorText, OnNewColor, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.OnGetDisplayName
<COMBINEWITH TJvGetColorNameEvent>
Summary
  Occurs immediately before an item is displayed in the color combobox.
Description
  Use OnGetDisplayName to customize an item before it is displayed in the color combobox. Set the 
  values of the parameters in the event handler so that the item appears correctly when it is displayed.
Parameters
  Sender      - The TJvColorComboBox component that has sent this event.
  Index       - Specifies the zero-based position of the color item in the combo box's list.
  Color       - Set Color to specify a new color for the to be displayed item. Leave Color unchanged
                to display the color as specified in the combo box's list.
  DisplayName - Set DisplayName to specify a new display name for the to be displayed item. Leave
                DisplayName unchanged to display the name as specified in the combo box's list.
See Also
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.OnInsertColor
<COMBINEWITH TJvNewColorEvent>
Summary
  Occurs immediately before a new item is inserted into the combo box's color list.
Description
  \Write an OnInsertColor event handler to conditionally prevent colors to be added to the color
  combo box, or to alter the DisplayName of a new color.
  
  Set AllowAdd to False to disallow the color to be added to the combo box's list.
Parameters
  Sender      - The TJvColorComboBox component that has sent this event.
  Color       - The new color added by the user.
  DisplayName - The display text for the new color. It consists of the NewColorText and a number
                indicating the number of custom colors added by the user, so far. Alter DisplayName
                to change the display text for the new color.
  AllowAdd    - Indicates whether the insert should be permitted.
See Also
  AddColor, InsertColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.OnNewColor
<COMBINEWITH TJvNewColorEvent>
Summary
  Occurs when the user tries to add a new color to the combo box.
Description
  \Write an OnNewColor event handler to conditionally prevent the user from adding colors to the
  color combo box, or to alter the DisplayName of a new color if the user adds it to the
  combo box.
  
  Set AllowAdd to False to disallow the user to add the color.
Parameters
  Sender      - The TJvColorComboBox component that has sent this event.
  Color       - The new color added by the user.
  DisplayName - The display text for the new color. It consists of the NewColorText and a number
                indicating the number of custom colors added by the user, so far. Alter DisplayName
                to change the display text for the new color.
  AllowAdd    - Indicates whether the add should be permitted.
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't allow colors to be added
  by the user.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, CustomColorCount, NewColorText, OnBeforeCustom, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.Options
Summary
  Determines the appearance and behavior of the color combo box.
Description
  Use the Options property to customize the appearance and functionality of the combo box.
  
  Use Options to
  
  * Specify how the color value must be displayed.
  * Enable the user to add colors to the combo box.
  * Add the system colors to the combo box.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, CustomColorCount, NewColorText, OnBeforeCustom, OnNewColor, TJvColorComboOption
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboOption
<TITLE TJvColorComboOption type>
<COMBINEWITH TJvColorComboOptions>
<AUTOLINK OFF>
Summary
  Defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a color combo box.
Description
<AUTOLINK ON>
  The \TJvColorComboOption type defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a color
  combo box.

  \TJvColorComboOptions is a set of \TJvColorComboOption values.

  The following table lists the possible values:
@@TJvColorComboOption.coText
  Displays the name of the color.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coHex
  Displays the hexadecimal value of the color.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coRGB
  Displays the RGB value of the color.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coSysColors
  Adds the system colors such as clWindow to the combo box.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coCustomColors
  Allows the user to add colors to the combo box, by selecting the special combo box item with text
  ColorDialogText.
<AUTOLINK OFF>
See Also
  TJvColorComboBox.Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboOptions
<TITLE TJvColorComboOptions type>
<AUTOLINK OFF>
